---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="This site is built to meet WCAG 2.2 Level AA. Here is what that means and how to report an accessibility barrier."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Accessibility statement</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        We want everyone to be able to find help and information here, regardless
        of how they use the web. This site is built to meet WCAG 2.2 Level AA.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Use clear, semantic structure so screen readers can navigate easily.</li>
        <li>Make every interactive element reachable and operable with a keyboard, with a visible focus indicator.</li>
        <li>Meet AA color-contrast levels for text and interface elements.</li>
        <li>Provide text alternatives for meaningful images.</li>
        <li>Keep the layout predictable, with no surprise pop-ups, autoplaying media, or motion. We honor your "reduce motion" setting.</li>
        <li>Offer a plain list of all states and territories as an alternative to the map.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Ongoing work</h2>
      <p>
        Accessibility is not a one-time task. We test pages with automated tools
        and by keyboard and screen reader, and we keep improving. Some content is
        still being built; we apply the same standards as we add it.
      </p>

      <h2>Report a barrier</h2>
      <p>
        If anything on this site is hard to use or get to, we want to know. Please
        <a href="/about">contact us</a> and describe what happened and which page
        you were on. We will work to fix it and to help you get the information you
        need in the meantime.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
